CatDescriptText: Cutline of related images published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, April 5, 1941, pg. 12 reads: "National Officers, Delegates And Visitors To Debs About Town Confab In Pittsburgh"
TitMainTitle: Three women including Barbara Jones on left wearing suit with fur collar and corsage, and possibly Helen Phillips in center, posed on sidewalk in front of block wall with urn, for Debs About Town conference
